# roomPRE
clr
gs 'statPRE'
fcolor = rgb(0, 0, 0)
bcolor = rgb(255, 255, 255)
lcolor = rgb(106, 90, 205)
'<center><b><font color="maroon">Apartment</font></b></center>'
'<center><img src="images/picPRE/room.jpg"></center>'

if pre = 0:
	pre = 1
	'You wake up to the sound of your alarm clock. You hear Luda, your wife, next to you mumbling something about "don''t want to" and "too early", then she pulls her blanket up and rolls over. You reach over to your clock and turn it of. <i>There are days, I just want to keep on sleeping</i>, you think to yourself. <i>But it''s not going to happen today.</i>'

	act 'Go to the bathroom':
		cla
		*clr
		minut += 30
		clr
		gs 'statPRE'
		'<center><img src="images/picPRE/self.jpg"></center>'
		'Quietly, so that you won''t wake up your daughter, you go to the bathroom and take care of your morning routine.'

		act 'Leave the apartment':
			cla
			*clr
			minut += 5
			clr
			gs 'statPRE'
			'<center><img src="images/picPRE/carPRE1.jpg"></center>'
			'In the parking lot near the house stands your car. As you approach it, press the button on your key and unlock it.'

			act 'Go to work':
				cla
				*clr
				minut += 25
				clr
				gs 'statPRE'
				'<center><img src="images/picPRE/carPRE.jpg"></center>'
				'You get behind the wheel, turn the key to start the car and drive off to work. The roads are filled with cars, but it''s the morning rush hour, so what else to expect. You drive for approximately an eternity, plus/minus and hour, but you eventually reach your office. At least the music on the radio was pleasent.'

				act 'Park at the office':
					cla
					*clr
					minut += 60
					clr
					gs 'statPRE'
					'<center><img src="images/picPRE/officePRE.jpg"></center>'
					'You pull into the parking lot near the office and manage to find a good parking spot. You greet the security guard on your way into the building and go upstairs, into your office.'
					'Shortly after you sat down at your desk and booted up your office computer, your bosses secretary comes in and hands your folder with several travel documents.' 
					'"Am I going on business trip or something?" you ask her.' 
					'"Yes, Boss said it had something to do with a construction project outside somewhere in the middle of nowhere, but that''s pretty much all I know" Oksana said.' 
					'After she left, you read over the travel documents and fill them out. Time to go to the director.'

					act 'Go to your Boss':
						cla
						*clr
						minut += 20
						clr
						gs 'statPRE'
						'<center><img src="images/picPRE/man.jpg"></center>'
						'You head into the office of the Director, you greet him and give him the papers to sign. Roman Gromov scans through the text before giving his wide authoritative stroke.'
						'"Ms. Glavbukh is probably already in the office. Go get the travel money while I make a few calls. We''ll discuss your trip when you get back." Roman said.'

						act 'Go to the chief accountant for travel':
							cla
							*clr
							minut += 30
							money += 15000
							clr
							gs 'statPRE'
							'<center><img src="images/picPRE/glavbuh.jpg"></center>'
							'Marina is indeed already in the office. After filing the signed travel form, she grumbles a bit before giving you money.'

							act 'Go back to the director':
								cla
								*clr
								minut += 15
								clr
								gs 'statPRE'
								'<center><img src="images/picPRE/man.jpg"></center>'
								'When you enter the director''s office again, Roman Gromov talks on the phone and gestured you to sit down on one of the chairs across from him.'
								'"Yes, I understand...yes. I will send Michael over ASAP, he''ll represent me. ...Yes... Tell your men to work on some other parts of the project in the meantime. Have Igor guard the pit and let no one make any fuss, make sure noone gets wind and, you know, try to halt the construction. ...Okay, we''ll keep in touch." Roman hangs up.'
								'Roman turns to you. "Last night, while excavating the pit for the base, the workers stumbled upon something. One of the Excavators dug into a hollow space of some sort. Igor was luckily close by and realized he needed to stop the excavation. Damn! It is not clear on what it is exactly. Maybe an abandoned bunker or something . But in any case if there are any more open chambers under the foundation, further construction of the complex may not be possible. So what I want you to do is to go to the construction site, figure out what it is and solve this mess as quickly as possible."'

								act 'I should at least meet':
									cla
									*clr
									minut += 5
									clr
									gs 'statPRE'
									'<center><img src="images/picPRE/man.jpg"></center>'
									'"I think we should get-" you say, but are quickly interrupted by your boss.'
									'"Michael, do you realize what''s at stake here? We''re near the end of our credit line, we still have unfinalized agreements on the projects contract and we already have guys digging the pit. You understand that if there''s a too big a hole under the foundation, we cannot continue building and find ourselves on the brink of ruin. So this mysterious structure situation must be addressed immediately. I have to stay here to keep a lid on things and buy us the time"'

									act 'Okay, then I will not waste any more time':gt 'roadPRE'
								end
							end
						end
					end
				end
			end
		end
	end
end
